PATTERN 9 — STRATEGY
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Intent: Define a family of algorithms, encapsulate each one, and make them interchangeable.
Use when: Sorting strategies, compression algorithms, authentication methods, payment gateways.
Do NOT use when: There is only one algorithm — do not over-engineer.

    // Modern C++ version using std::function (no inheritance required)
    class Sorter {
    public:
        using Strategy = std::function<void(std::vector<int>&)>;
        explicit Sorter(Strategy s) : strategy_(std::move(s)) {}
        void sort(std::vector<int>& v) { strategy_(v); }
    private:
        Strategy strategy_;
    };

    // Usage:
    Sorter ascending([](auto& v){ std::sort(v.begin(), v.end()); });
    Sorter descending([](auto& v){ std::sort(v.rbegin(), v.rend()); });

