PATTERN 14 — CRTP (Curiously Recurring Template Pattern)
─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
Intent: Achieve static polymorphism (compile-time virtual dispatch) with zero runtime overhead.
Use when: Performance-critical polymorphism (game engines, numeric libraries, policy classes).
Do NOT use when: Runtime polymorphism is needed (types not known at compile time) — use virtual.

    template <typename Derived>
    class Printable {
    public:
        void print() const {
            static_cast<const Derived*>(this)->printImpl();
        }
    };

    class Foo : public Printable<Foo> {
    public:
        void printImpl() const { std::cout << "Foo\n"; }
    };

    class Bar : public Printable<Bar> {
    public:
        void printImpl() const { std::cout << "Bar\n"; }
    };

    template <typename T>
    void printAll(const Printable<T>& p) { p.print(); }

